#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:3
msgid "Twin Delayed DDPG"
msgstr "雙延遲 DDPG (Twin Delayed DDPG)"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:5
msgid "Table of Contents"
msgstr "目錄"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:8
msgid "Background"
msgstr "背景"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:10
msgid "(Previously: `Background for DDPG`_)"
msgstr "（先前章節：`Background for DDPG`_）"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:14
msgid ""
"While DDPG can achieve great performance sometimes, it is frequently "
"brittle with respect to hyperparameters and other kinds of tuning. A "
"common failure mode for DDPG is that the learned Q-function begins to "
"dramatically overestimate Q-values, which then leads to the policy "
"breaking, because it exploits the errors in the Q-function. Twin Delayed "
"DDPG (TD3) is an algorithm that addresses this issue by introducing three"
" critical tricks:"
msgstr ""
"雖然 DDPG 有時能達到優異的性能，但它在超參數和其他調整方面經常很脆弱。DDPG 的"
"一個常見失敗模式是：學到的 Q 函數 (Q-Function) 開始大幅高估 Q 值，進而導致策"
"略崩潰，因為它利用了 Q 函數中的誤差。雙延遲 DDPG (TD3) 是一種透過引入三個關"
"鍵技巧來解決這個問題的演算法："

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:16
msgid ""
"**Trick One: Clipped Double-Q Learning.** TD3 learns *two* Q-functions "
"instead of one (hence \"twin\"), and uses the smaller of the two Q-values"
" to form the targets in the Bellman error loss functions."
msgstr ""
"**技巧一：截斷雙 Q 學習 (Clipped Double-Q Learning)。** TD3 學習*兩個* Q 函"
"數而不是一個（因此稱為「雙」），並使用兩個 Q 值中較小的那個來構成 Bellman 誤"
"差損失函數中的目標值。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:18
msgid ""
"**Trick Two: \"Delayed\" Policy Updates.** TD3 updates the policy (and "
"target networks) less frequently than the Q-function. The paper "
"recommends one policy update for every two Q-function updates."
msgstr ""
"**技巧二：「延遲」策略更新。** TD3 更新策略（和目標網路 (Target Network)）的"
"頻率低於 Q 函數。論文建議每兩次 Q 函數更新進行一次策略更新。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:20
msgid ""
"**Trick Three: Target Policy Smoothing.** TD3 adds noise to the target "
"action, to make it harder for the policy to exploit Q-function errors by "
"smoothing out Q along changes in action."
msgstr ""
"**技巧三：目標策略平滑化 (Target Policy Smoothing)。** TD3 對目標動作添加雜"
"訊，透過沿動作變化方向平滑 Q 值，使策略更難利用 Q 函數的誤差。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:22
msgid ""
"Together, these three tricks result in substantially improved performance"
" over baseline DDPG."
msgstr "這三個技巧結合在一起，使得性能相較於基線 DDPG 有了大幅提升。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:25
msgid "Quick Facts"
msgstr "快速概覽"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:27
msgid "TD3 is an off-policy algorithm."
msgstr "TD3 是一種離策略 (Off-policy) 演算法。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:28
msgid "TD3 can only be used for environments with continuous action spaces."
msgstr "TD3 只能用於具有連續動作空間 (Action Space) 的環境。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:29
msgid "The Spinning Up implementation of TD3 does not support parallelization."
msgstr "Spinning Up 的 TD3 實作不支援平行化。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:32
msgid "Key Equations"
msgstr "關鍵方程式"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:34
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"TD3 concurrently learns two Q-functions, :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}` and "
":math:`Q_{\\phi_2}`, by mean square Bellman error minimization, in almost"
" the same way that DDPG learns its single Q-function. To show exactly how"
" TD3 does this and how it differs from normal DDPG, we'll work from the "
"innermost part of the loss function outwards."
msgstr ""
"TD3 透過均方 Bellman 誤差最小化同時學習兩個 Q 函數 :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}` 和 "
":math:`Q_{\\phi_2}`，方式與 DDPG 學習其單一 Q 函數幾乎相同。為了精確展示 TD3 "
"如何做到這一點以及它與一般 DDPG 的不同之處，我們將從損失函數的最內層向外推導。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:36
msgid ""
"First: **target policy smoothing**. Actions used to form the Q-learning "
"target are based on the target policy, "
":math:`\\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}`, but with clipped noise added on "
"each dimension of the action. After adding the clipped noise, the target "
"action is then clipped to lie in the valid action range (all valid "
"actions, :math:`a`, satisfy :math:`a_{Low} \\leq a \\leq a_{High}`). The "
"target actions are thus:"
msgstr ""
"首先：**目標策略平滑化**。用於構成 Q-learning 目標值的動作基於目標策略 "
":math:`\\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}`，但在動作的每個維度上添加了截斷雜訊。添"
"加截斷雜訊後，目標動作再被截斷到有效動作範圍內（所有有效動作 :math:`a` 滿足 "
":math:`a_{Low} \\leq a \\leq a_{High}`）。因此目標動作為："

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:38
msgid ""
"a'(s') = \\text{clip}\\left(\\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}(s') + "
"\\text{clip}(\\epsilon,-c,c), a_{Low}, a_{High}\\right), \\;\\;\\;\\;\\; "
"\\epsilon \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, \\sigma)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:42
msgid ""
"Target policy smoothing essentially serves as a regularizer for the "
"algorithm. It addresses a particular failure mode that can happen in "
"DDPG: if the Q-function approximator develops an incorrect sharp peak for"
" some actions, the policy will quickly exploit that peak and then have "
"brittle or incorrect behavior. This can be averted by smoothing out the "
"Q-function over similar actions, which target policy smoothing is "
"designed to do."
msgstr ""
"目標策略平滑化本質上是演算法的一種正則化手段。它解決了 DDPG 中可能發生的一種"
"特定失敗模式：如果 Q 函數近似器對某些動作產生了不正確的尖銳峰值，策略會迅速利"
"用該峰值，導致脆弱或不正確的行為。透過在相似動作上平滑 Q 函數可以避免這種情"
"況，而這正是目標策略平滑化的設計目的。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:44
msgid ""
"Next: **clipped double-Q learning**. Both Q-functions use a single "
"target, calculated using whichever of the two Q-functions gives a smaller"
" target value:"
msgstr ""
"接下來：**截斷雙 Q 學習**。兩個 Q 函數使用同一個目標值，該目標值使用兩個 Q "
"函數中給出較小目標值的那個來計算："

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:46
msgid ""
"y(r,s',d) = r + \\gamma (1 - d) \\min_{i=1,2} Q_{\\phi_{i, "
"\\text{targ}}}(s', a'(s')),"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:50
msgid "and then both are learned by regressing to this target:"
msgstr "然後兩者都透過回歸到這個目標值來學習："

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:52
msgid ""
"L(\\phi_1, {\\mathcal D}) = \\underE{(s,a,r,s',d) \\sim {\\mathcal D}}{\n"
"    \\Bigg( Q_{\\phi_1}(s,a) - y(r,s',d) \\Bigg)^2\n"
"    },"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:58
msgid ""
"L(\\phi_2, {\\mathcal D}) = \\underE{(s,a,r,s',d) \\sim {\\mathcal D}}{\n"
"    \\Bigg( Q_{\\phi_2}(s,a) - y(r,s',d) \\Bigg)^2\n"
"    }."
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:64
msgid ""
"Using the smaller Q-value for the target, and regressing towards that, "
"helps fend off overestimation in the Q-function."
msgstr "使用較小的 Q 值作為目標值並向其回歸，有助於抑制 Q 函數的高估問題。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:66
#, python-brace-format
msgid "Lastly: the policy is learned just by maximizing :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}`:"
msgstr "最後：策略僅透過最大化 :math:`Q_{\\phi_1}` 來學習："

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:68
msgid ""
"\\max_{\\theta} \\underset{s \\sim {\\mathcal D}}{{\\mathrm E}}\\left[ "
"Q_{\\phi_1}(s, \\mu_{\\theta}(s)) \\right],"
msgstr ""

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:72
msgid ""
"which is pretty much unchanged from DDPG. However, in TD3, the policy is "
"updated less frequently than the Q-functions are. This helps damp the "
"volatility that normally arises in DDPG because of how a policy update "
"changes the target."
msgstr ""
"這與 DDPG 幾乎沒有變化。然而，在 TD3 中，策略的更新頻率低於 Q 函數。這有助於"
"抑制 DDPG 中通常因策略更新改變目標值而產生的波動性。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:76
msgid "Exploration vs. Exploitation"
msgstr "探索與利用"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:78
msgid ""
"TD3 trains a deterministic policy in an off-policy way. Because the "
"policy is deterministic, if the agent were to explore on-policy, in the "
"beginning it would probably not try a wide enough variety of actions to "
"find useful learning signals. To make TD3 policies explore better, we add"
" noise to their actions at training time, typically uncorrelated mean-"
"zero Gaussian noise. To facilitate getting higher-quality training data, "
"you may reduce the scale of the noise over the course of training. (We do"
" not do this in our implementation, and keep noise scale fixed "
"throughout.)"
msgstr ""
"TD3 以離策略的方式訓練一個確定性策略 (Deterministic Policy)。因為策略是確定性"
"的，如果代理程式進行同策略探索 (Exploration)，在初期可能不會嘗試足夠多樣的動"
"作來找到有用的學習信號。為了讓 TD3 策略更好地探索，我們在訓練時為動作添加雜"
"訊，通常是不相關的零均值高斯雜訊。為了促進獲得更高品質的訓練資料，你可以在訓"
"練過程中逐步降低雜訊的強度。（我們在實作中不這樣做，在整個訓練過程中保持雜訊"
"強度固定。）"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:80
msgid ""
"At test time, to see how well the policy exploits what it has learned, we"
" do not add noise to the actions."
msgstr "在測試時，為了觀察策略如何利用 (Exploitation) 所學到的知識，我們不對動作添加雜訊。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:82 ../../algorithms/td3.rst:142
msgid "You Should Know"
msgstr "你應該知道"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:84
msgid ""
"Our TD3 implementation uses a trick to improve exploration at the start "
"of training. For a fixed number of steps at the beginning (set with the "
"``start_steps`` keyword argument), the agent takes actions which are "
"sampled from a uniform random distribution over valid actions. After "
"that, it returns to normal TD3 exploration."
msgstr ""
"我們的 TD3 實作使用了一個技巧來改善訓練初期的探索。在開始的固定步數內（透過"
" ``start_steps`` 關鍵字引數設定），代理程式從有效動作的均勻隨機分佈中取樣動"
"作。之後，它恢復到正常的 TD3 探索方式。"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:88
msgid "Pseudocode"
msgstr "虛擬碼"

#: ../../algorithms/td3.rst:91
msgid ""
"\\begin{algorithm}[H]\n"
"    \\caption{Twin Delayed DDPG}\n"
"    \\label{alg1}\n"
"\\begin{algorithmic}[1]\n"
"    \\STATE Input: initial policy parameters $\\theta$, Q-function "
"parameters $\\phi_1$, $\\phi_2$, empty replay buffer $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"    \\STATE Set target parameters equal to main parameters "
"$\\theta_{\\text{targ}} \\leftarrow \\theta$, $\\phi_{\\text{targ},1} "
"\\leftarrow \\phi_1$, $\\phi_{\\text{targ},2} \\leftarrow \\phi_2$\n"
"    \\REPEAT\n"
"        \\STATE Observe state $s$ and select action $a = "
"\\text{clip}(\\mu_{\\theta}(s) + \\epsilon, a_{Low}, a_{High})$, where "
"$\\epsilon \\sim \\mathcal{N}$\n"
"        \\STATE Execute $a$ in the environment\n"
"        \\STATE Observe next state $s'$, reward $r$, and done signal $d$ "
"to indicate whether $s'$ is terminal\n"
"        \\STATE Store $(s,a,r,s',d)$ in replay buffer $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"        \\STATE If $s'$ is terminal, reset environment state.\n"
"        \\IF{it's time to update}\n"
"            \\FOR{$j$ in range(however many updates)}\n"
"                \\STATE Randomly sample a batch of transitions, $B = \\{ "
"(s,a,r,s',d) \\}$ from $\\mathcal{D}$\n"
"                \\STATE Compute target actions\n"
"                \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                    a'(s') = "
"\\text{clip}\\left(\\mu_{\\theta_{\\text{targ}}}(s') + "
"\\text{clip}(\\epsilon,-c,c), a_{Low}, a_{High}\\right), \\;\\;\\;\\;\\; "
"\\epsilon \\sim \\mathcal{N}(0, \\sigma)\n"
"                \\end{equation*}\n"
"                \\STATE Compute targets\n"
"                \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                    y(r,s',d) = r + \\gamma (1-d) \\min_{i=1,2} "
"Q_{\\phi_{\\text{targ},i}}(s', a'(s'))\n"
"                \\end{equation*}\n"
"                \\STATE Update Q-functions by one step of gradient "
"descent using\n"
"                \\begin{align*}\n"
"                    & \\nabla_{\\phi_i} \\frac{1}{|B|}\\sum_{(s,a,r,s',d)"
" \\in B} \\left( Q_{\\phi_i}(s,a) - y(r,s',d) \\right)^2 && \\text{for } "
"i=1,2\n"
"                \\end{align*}\n"
"                \\IF{ $j \\mod$ \\texttt{policy\\_delay} $ = 0$}\n"
"                    \\STATE Update policy by one step of gradient ascent "
"using\n"
"                    \\begin{equation*}\n"
"                        \\nabla_{\\theta} \\frac{1}{|B|}\\sum_{s \\in "
"B}Q_{\\phi_1}(s, \\mu_{\\theta}(s))\n"
"                    \\end{equation*}\n"
"                    \\STATE Update target networks with\n"
"                    \\begin{align*}\n"
"                        \\phi_{\\text{targ},i} &\\leftarrow \\rho "
"\\phi_{\\text{targ}, i} + (1-\\rho) \\phi_i && \\text{for } i=1,2\\\\\n"
"                        \\theta_{\\text{targ}} &\\leftarrow \\rho "
"\\theta_{\\text{targ}} + (1-\\rho) \\theta\n"
"                    \\end{align*}\n"
"                \\ENDIF\n"
"            \\ENDFOR\n"
"        \\ENDIF\n"
"    \\UNTIL{convergence}\n"
"\\end{algorithmic}\n"
"\\end{algorithm}"
msgstr ""

